 the start of their last semester of attendance at VMI  All first class cadets are provided with the Application for Graduation form at the time of their enrollment in the Fall semester  and in the Spring semester for readmitted cadets  It is the responsibility of the cadet to assure that they have appropriately filed in order to be tracked for degree completion  Additionally  cadets should keep the Registrar s Office informed of changes to anticipated completion so all official records can be updated and completion monitored appropriately  The deadline for submission of all requests for additional majors and or minors are due into the Registrar s Office the last regular VMI semester preceding the official date of graduation  December Candidates   Spring Semester May Candidates   Fall Semester September  December and January Candidates   Spring Semester Transfer Credit Requirements  It is the responsibility of the cadet to assure that all courses transferred in to meet graduation requirements are pre approved prior to their being taken and completed  This must be done through the appropriate academic department head  and in writing on the Course Approval for Transfer Credit Form  DEADLINE FOR GRADE SUBMISSION  Cadets are required to get all official grade completion results into the Registrar s Office  303 Shell Hall  Lexington  Virginia 24450 at least one week prior to the certification of the degree  VMI holds two commencement ceremonies   one in December and one in May  Questions regarding commencement may be directed to the Chief of Staff Office at 540 464 7104  or click here for email inquiries  Cadet questions regarding graduation status can be addressed with LTC William Oliver Associate Registrar 303 Shell Hall Lexington  VA 24450 Phone  540 464 7191 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The 